</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9B3C8793966029A4F8DADBE0BCB1EDED" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="E752A327A011C99232825553E6BDB1F8" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C05AA64F31BEA567DEBC7896F829D21C" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">
This species is known from Minas Gerais, Brazil (
<bibRefCitation id="1714A510E95700931D01329F8966FE41" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" author="Arruda, MCC" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="1378 - 1361" refId="B5" refString="Arruda, MCC, Sepuvelda, GF, Miller, RNG, Ferreira, MASV, Santiago, DVR, Resende, MLV, Dianese, JC, Felipe, MSS, 2005. Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data. Mycologia 97: 1378 - 1361, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" title="Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" volume="97" year="2005">Arruda et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C0CA5D598CF665FAA98414963C1BFEA0" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" type="observations">
<paragraph id="FA684750CF8857A46AE98AA26835FB80" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Observations.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="05E7EE226F31C35F0243706DFBA1A1F4" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">
<taxonomicName id="3186381D3324A5A6EE88657886C27C0C" authorityName="Niveiro, Lodge &amp; Aime" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Arruda, G. F. Sepulveda, R. N. G. Miller, M. A. Ferreira &amp; M. S. Felipe" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Moniliophthora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Moniliophthora brasiliensis" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="821EB29D55ECC7AE8EC1AF58FB5ECC83" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Moniliophthora brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the light pink to crimson red pileus surface, ellipsoidal basidiospores, 10-14 
<normalizedToken id="85026903EDB97D8C86C66D497FF1F89E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-7 
<normalizedToken id="6C023221D84B3FE40DB83B0C410735F4" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, and lageniform cheilocystidia, with a thin apex, 28-37 
<normalizedToken id="EBA51FF09F719358324B3AEA436AF270" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10-16 
<normalizedToken id="587726CBBF6BFB98C3E1167550C01C04" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in size (
<bibRefCitation id="F7C4D149FF7BD10777BE5CB62305BBA1" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" author="Arruda, MCC" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="1378 - 1361" refId="B5" refString="Arruda, MCC, Sepuvelda, GF, Miller, RNG, Ferreira, MASV, Santiago, DVR, Resende, MLV, Dianese, JC, Felipe, MSS, 2005. Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data. Mycologia 97: 1378 - 1361, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" title="Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" volume="97" year="2005">Arruda et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="9693D99384BD676CBCD6021D7CEE519E" authorityName="Niveiro, Lodge &amp; Aime" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Arruda, G. F. Sepulveda, R. N. G. Miller, M. A. Ferreira &amp; M. S. Felipe" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Moniliophthora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Moniliophthora brasiliensis" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="5E92322EC2DB38086A08057593BD9795" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Moniliophthora brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a parasite of 
<taxonomicName id="9F8553745EF60AD67AC64A2E3B1A9418" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Heteropterys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heteropterys acutifolia" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutifolia">
<emphasis id="C697EC58C5FAD2D656D31B9A50139D6B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Heteropterys acutifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="B477ABA74152ADFA403CAF7837DDB406" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Heteropterys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Malpighiaceae</taxonomicName>
). Only ITS sequence data are available for this taxon, which was derived from a dikaryotic basidiome collected from a necrotic broom on 
<taxonomicName id="4B5E6C4A58F633B4B91BC866882F2EC1" genus="H." lsidName="H. acutifolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="acutifolia">
<emphasis id="439E5846BC97228F862AF45DAFB176F2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">H. acutifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A58A6A1AB56BE6FE9754EA93555B7CB2" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" author="Arruda, MCC" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="1378 - 1361" refId="B5" refString="Arruda, MCC, Sepuvelda, GF, Miller, RNG, Ferreira, MASV, Santiago, DVR, Resende, MLV, Dianese, JC, Felipe, MSS, 2005. Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data. Mycologia 97: 1378 - 1361, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" title="Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" volume="97" year="2005">Arruda et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="099770F83BA96A06CE995ECEEB62D0AE" authorityName="Niveiro, Lodge &amp; Aime" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Arruda, G. F. Sepulveda, R. N. G. Miller, M. A. Ferreira &amp; M. S. Felipe" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Moniliophthora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Moniliophthora brasiliensis" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="EE8126DAC01E14F0ED113E3AB5710C8D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">Moniliophthora brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is extremely similar to 
<taxonomicName id="45FAB880EC0BA668011835C6FADFE85E" genus="M." lsidName="M. perniciosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="perniciosa">
<emphasis id="4D62C7436B80C1B8EBD332E2EDAC9E3F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="39">M. perniciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and diagnosis between the two species at present is based soley on differences in ITS sequence data (
<bibRefCitation id="4A5C5EFBD20C63EBFD209FD6CE89407D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" author="Arruda, MCC" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="39" pagination="1378 - 1361" refId="B5" refString="Arruda, MCC, Sepuvelda, GF, Miller, RNG, Ferreira, MASV, Santiago, DVR, Resende, MLV, Dianese, JC, Felipe, MSS, 2005. Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data. Mycologia 97: 1378 - 1361, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" title="Crinipellis brasiliensis, a new species based on morphological and molecular data." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/mycologia.97.6.1348" volume="97" year="2005">Arruda et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
